		   <table class="mform"  border="0" cellpadding="1" cellspacing="0" width="100%">
		   <tr><td class="headerrow" colspan="2" class="mform" valign="top" id="forumSubject">
		   <span class="sm">Posted @ Tue, Mar 15th 1:50 PM2005 </span><span id="notbold">| <span class="sm">IP: Logged</span> | <a class="sm" href="/forum.html?forum=1&mid=111090675268808426&num=4&page=0&post=1&replyto=1110912566746058707"><img src="/shared/reply_to_thread_ico.gif" border="0" alt="Reply..." height="11" width="17" /> Reply to this</a></a>    <a name=1110912566746058707></a></small></td></tr>
		   <tr><td valign="top" id="fs8" class="mform" ><span id="notbold">By:</span> <a href="/db/poster.html?user=170952"><span id=Scholar>cafeenoftheazurestorm</span></a><b><span id=Scholar><br>Scholar</span></b><br /><img src="/shared/user_star_ico.gif" height="9" width="9" alt="*" /><img src="/shared/user_star_ico.gif" height="9" width="9" alt="*" /><br />547 posts
		   <br /><nobr><span id="notbold">Score</span>: Good [3.54]</nobr><br /><br /><a href="/cgi-bin/pm.pl?action=addtolist&addname=cafeenoftheazurestorm&type=Address" id="fs8"><img src="/shared/plus.gif" border="0" align="middle" height="9" width="9" alt="Add to address book"> Add to address book</a><br /><img src="/shared/transp.gif" width="135" border="0" height="1"></td><td valign="top" class="mform" width="100%"><p>The potion belt default is Shift-P.<br><br>To use it, simply drop a potion into one of the active slots (yes, 2 are grayed out at the beginning). You can then make a hotkey for that slot by simply clicking and holding.<br><br>Where the belt really shines is in 2 places.<br><br>1) You do not need to move the potion out of a bag to use it. This means that you can still use one of the potions there without swapping a bag and a potion and all that.<br><br>2) It works with multiple instances of the same potion. More clearly, if you buy 12 Cloudy Potions (Single charge, insta-cast invis) and place one of them into the belt, you will see a 12 in the corner. Each time you use one of them, it will count down. You no longer have to search through your inventory for one of them.<br><br>It will also remember what was last placed in that slot. So, if you run out of cloudy potions and buy more, you don't have to set up the belt again.</p><br /><span class="sm">----------------------------</span><br /><span class="sm">~WoW~<br><a href="HTTP://wow.allakhazam.com/profile.html?81141" target="akztarg">Cafeen</a> - Troll Hunter<br>&lt;<a href="HTTP://thefoot.guildwizard.com" target="akztarg">The Foot Clan</a>&gt;<br>Deathwing (PvP)<br><br>~EQ~<br><b><a href="HTTP://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=892149" target="akztarg">Stubbed Toez</a></b> - Overlord of Brell<br><b><a href="HTTP://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=283557" target="akztarg">Cafeen</a></b>- Tier'Dal Coercer<br>Member of &lt;<a href="HTTP://www.deluclin.com" target="akztarg">Descending Essence</a>&gt;<br>Luclin Server</span class="sm"></td></td></tr><tr><td colspan="2" class="mform"><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" width="100%"><tr><td id="fs8">Posting from the couch</td></tr></table>
